  "body": "RPC doesn't check if the 'value' of transaction is negative (the value can also become negative if JSON number > 2^63 is used instead of string). This causes it to write an empty block to the block chain (chain_manager.go write, does not check here too), and this leads to crash when trying to get parent like can be seen from stack trace.\n\n```\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/core.CalcGasLimit(0x0, 0xeb2c40a41c2c098e)\n        /home/sami/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/core/chain_manager.go:64 +0x34\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner.(*worker).makeCurrent(0xc2080e5ea0)\n        /home/sami/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner/worker.go:296 +0x7ee\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner.(*worker).commitNewWork(0xc2080e5ea0)\n        /home/sami/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner/worker.go:320 +0x13d\ngithub.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner.(*worker).update(0xc2080e5ea0)\n        /home/sami/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner/worker.go:191 +0x364\ncreated by github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner.newWorker\n        /home/sami/go-ethereum/build/_workspace/src/github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/miner/worker.go:120 +0x310\n```\n",
